<html>
<body>
<h1>Assertions Module - Report</h1>

Maximum quantity of assertions by tests defined by user: <%= @quantity_of_assertions_user_input %>
<br><br>
Total of existing tests found: <%= @total_of_existing_tests %>
<br><br>
Total of assertions found: <%= @total_of_assertions %>
<br><br>
<% if @total_of_assertions > @total_of_existing_tests*3 %>
	<div style="background-color:red;border:1px solid black;padding:10px;">
	You should spend some time to review your test suite. It seems you have too many assertions!
	</div>
<% elsif @total_of_assertions < @total_of_existing_tests %>
	<div style="background-color:red;border:1px solid black;padding:10px;">
	You should spend some time to review your test suite. It seems you don't have at least one assertion per test scenario!	
	</div>
<% else %>
	<div style="background-color:green;border:1px solid black;padding:10px;">
	It seems your quantity of assertions per test is OK. Good work! ;)
	</div>
<% end %>
</body>
</html>

